 @LPno.9 Just because you can be brought up with and around certain customs and beliefs does not stop a person from exercising their own sense of morality for better or for worse. 
Slavery was a common practice in America before the Civil War. But eventually enough people said “Hey, this is barbaric, unjust, and immoral, and we should put an end to it.” As did most civilizations at some point in their histories. 
Having respect and empathy for human life is the way we change evil practices. It’s just that people with power and privilege either benefit from those systems, or are so far removed from them that they don’t see how awful it is, and would much rather remain ignorant. Cultural specifics are meaningless when they’re used as an excuse to brutalize human beings, or as a means of deflecting the blame from allowing those practices to continue.

 @4ng3legg  That boy is Samwell Blackwood, and the douche is Amos Bracken. In the book they did have a duel for Rhaenyra's hand in marriage but no one died, and Samwell actually lost.

House Bracken later supported the greens, the Blackwoods the blacks. Amos and Samwell fought again, and Samwell lost again and was killed. Amos was immediately killed afterwards by an arrow headshot from Samwell's sister Alysanne (aka Black Aly). The Brackens then surrendered after their seat Stone Hedge was sieged and taken.

Black Aly and Samwell's 11-year-old son Benjicot then commanded the rivermen forces and wiped out the Baratheon main force, effectively destroying the last greens fighting strength and ending the rule of Aegon II.

