 @thisguy8106  "The Hightowers Lust for power was what started the war. "
Wrong. Rhaenyra's selfishness, decadence and refusal to put the needs of the realm above her own lusts and pleasure started the war. Alicent was fully willing to support Rhaenyra, but Rhaenyra proved herself to be selfish and treacherous and willing to place a bomb under her own house just for a night of pleasure. That's what turned Alicent against her, she realizes Rhaenyra is going to be a disastrous queen, which will be proven correct later on in this series.
The war ultimately starts because Rhaenyra is passing off bastards as heirs to the throne, which creates a major legitimacy question for her children. That's what ultimately fuels all the drama we see going on right now.

